reviews.title: Best local in town!
reviews.text: The best local in town! Talked to locals, apparently we were very lucky! The Waiting time is very long, but it pays off! Food very good, Mood pleasant, service courteous! Have eaten one of the best steaks in my life!!! (01.08.25)

reviews.title: Laid back luxury
reviews.text: A lovely place. Takes no reservations but they have plenty of seating,  especially if the weather is good. If you have to wait they have a nice waiting area where you can enjoy mine nibbles and a drink. Extensive wine menu. I was lucky to be sat at the bar so I could see the hustle and bustle. Very friendly and good service. Food was delicious. Fish excellent and meat cooked exactly the way I had ordered. Nice laid back atmosphere.

reviews.title: A wonderful, busy, FABULOUS place
reviews.text:
This place is 'gezellig' on steroids! It exudes positive energy and bonhomie from the people working there and the other guests. It felt almost as if I'd been admitted to one of the best parties I've ever been to.
This atmosphere was matched by friendly, efficient, attentive service - despite the place being jam packed (which added to the pleasure).
Moules were on the menu as they're just in season and everything you'd want.
Paired with a bottle of Albarino (between us), it was one of the most enjoyable evenings I have experienced in many years

reviews.title: Food fine; service very poor. Unfortunately.
reviews.text: This afternoon after EN walking through the city park (us, son, daughter-in-law and their 2 children) we had a bite to eat at café Sjiek. We come here all the time. But not been after sale a few months ago. The food: fine ... nothing wrong with that. DE operation: very heavy on DER the size ... downright very bad. From the moment we sat down, everything that could have gone wrong went wrong. Wrong dishes. DE e EN had already finished main course and DE other had nothing. A full sheet of booze was DE table EN partly about us. Excuses? Not a word at all!

reviews.title: Cozy, fine and tasty
reviews.text:
Great food, in a nice ambiance. Delicious buttery Black Angus steak with asparagus and string beans with pepper sauce, fries and butter lettuce and a fine red house wine. Extremely friendly and professional staff who visibly enjoy the work. Music in the background is also quite good, not too loud, nicely recognizable from Sting to Barbara Pravi, Fleetwood Mac and Tina Turner.
Special thanks for our waitress Guusje, who let us make the best choice for the menu based on our questions.

reviews.title: Great meal outdoors in a nice surrounding area
reviews.text: Had dinner with the traditional meat stew,  not a light dinner but a very good meal with a nice outdoor area and good service!

reviews.title: Irish coffee
reviews.text: Came especially for the super tasty Irish coffee but got none with the excuse that the lid of the shaker was gone 😅🙈

reviews.title: Just fine!
reviews.text: First time eaten since the takeover, come there for almost 30 years. Nice food and friendly service on a rainy Saturday afternoon. Just good and a constant address in Maastricht. Fine wines and champagnes

reviews.title: Finesse, conviviality and good food with a refined twist
reviews.text:
The menu has gone through a more luxurious shift with extra finesse in presentation and tastes.   
It still feels like the same Café Sjiek, only with a sophisticated twist. It was another pleasant find where you meet acquaintances and have a nice conversation with strangers. Chapeau.

reviews.title: Refined and successful twist
reviews.text:
Since Luca and Wouter took over, the menu has seen a subtle but noticeable shift, a touch more upscale, with added finesse in presentation and flavors. 

It’s clear they’ve brought fresh energy and ideas to the kitchen.

What’s great is that the beloved old atmosphere remains untouched. 

The warm, lively ambiance that made Café Sjiek a local favorite is still very much alive. 

It still feels like the same Café Sjiek, just with a refined twist.

reviews.title: Cozy and tasty
reviews.text:
Cozy and tasty as always. 
Only: way too small a bowl of fries for 4 people and if you reorder you have to pay extra for an extra portion! Foo!! Don't do that. It never was. Concept was rock solid. Please don't change

reviews.title: Enjoyed a wonderful evening
reviews.text:
Again had a wonderful evening!
Enjoyed the delicious dishes. The homemade shrimp croquettes are highly recommended!! The place has a cosy casual atmosphere. 
We will definitely be back again 🥂

reviews.title: Enjoy with a big G!
reviews.text: Last night really delicious food @ Cafe Sjiek. The appetizers were sublime, both the crab cocktail with jalapeño sauce, as the langoustines, as the veal sweetbread with pork belly, all prepared with class. Super taste. The mussels and the fries quite as they should be. The oysters beforehand with a blissful bubble completed the evening. Still nice after drinks with a delicious wine and good company. A Saturday night like we're only supposed to get a lot more.

reviews.title: Enjoy with big G!
reviews.text: Last night really delicious food @ Cafe Sjiek. The appetizers were sublime, both the crab cocktail with jalapeño foam, and the langoustines, as well as the veal sweetbread with pork belly were all prepared with class. Super taste. The mussels and fries quite as they should be. The oysters beforehand with a delicious bubble completed the evening. Still nice after drinks with a delicious wine and good company. A Saturday night like we're only supposed to get a lot more. Wouter & Luca our compliments! What hospitality! Great!

tips.body: Gewoon genieten van het eten en de heerlijke ambiance!

reviews.title: New owner, new concept .. now more high end restaurant
reviews.text:
Previously a cozy bar, where you could also eat really good quality food. No reservations possible but nobody cared :)  good value for money.
New owner has kept the interior, but it has now become a higher end restaurant in the 150 euro per couple range for standard dinner.
Staff is very friendly but very efficient … tell them to slow done, otherwise you will be out of the door again before you know it :)
There was also a “wait to be seated” sign, so the old days of walking into a packed bar-restaurant are no more …
Don’t get me wrong: great staff and great food as one would expect in a high end restaurant..

summaries.text: Set in the Heggenstraat, a cosy spot in the old city centre, is this pleasant restaurant with an atmospheric, baroque-style interior. It is immediately apparent that the kitchen is run by a young team – even if they do keep the flavours classic. The prices are very reasonable too!

Rodny Welters has created his own little world on the fifth floor of this factory building in Maastricht's Sphinxkwartier. Rugged surfaces meet stylish upholstery here in a tasteful symbiosis. All eyes are on the open kitchen, where chef Welters lets his cooking do the talking; his culinary creations draw inspiration from around the globe, underpinned by exquisite sauces. With dishes such as haddock à la meunière with a tandoori velouté or fried scampi with a red curry and coconut milk sauce, the "Experience" set menu certainly lives up to its name.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

Berlin is nothing if not resilient, having outlasted many turbulent periods in its history. Those scars still show today in the stark distinction felt between the east and west sides of the city even though it’s been decades since the Berlin Wall came down. And for a European capital city, it’s not conventionally beautiful like Paris or London. Instead, Berlin embraces its eccentric hodgepodge of grit and glamour.
